The paper deals with the complexity of clustering curves, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves the use of distance measures such as Frechet distance and Dynamic Time Warping, which are commonly studied in algorithms for time series analysis and similarity search, making cs.DS and cs.SI likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the NP-hardness and W[1]-hardness of the clustering problems, indicating a focus on computational complexity theory (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents approximation algorithms and exact algorithms for the clustering problems, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG a possible category as well.
